Bill,

I don&#39;t remember seeing much about it myself besides being mentioned in passing a couple times. If someone wants to get something like this started then we need to get a head count of participants. We need to get a commitment from each and announce the plan in advance to all those who want to participate. I&#39;m all for these validation exercises.

Regards,

Frank R.

----- Original Message ----
From: psi_research &lt;vilhellm@...&gt;
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Sent: Thursday, January 10, 2008 1:41:35 PM
Subject: [EVP-ITC] Re: the unlabeled files_results














            I must have missed the announced beginning of the experiment. Between

travel and getting over 100 new emails per day it must have slipped

by. I often don&#39;t get to hear the posted recordings until several days

after they are posted and that&#39;s assuming they are still on the mail

server.



If there is a set date when new unlabeled files will be posted I&#39;ll

set my calender and specifically download and listen in a timely

matter then post what I hear. Hopefully this would be after the 20th

of this month.  -Bill 



--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups .com, Ron Lederer &lt;ronriko@... &gt; wrote:

